Astrea of the Stars 04-Aug-21 10:52 PM
A typical meeting room. Somewhat. There are indeed chairs and tables, as you would expect - however, the table itself is basically one huge slab of metal (though it's cut so that there is decent legroom). The chairs that make up this room are also sort of... odd, being black leather chairs... that seem to be constrained to rolling around in a little tiny 'box' of sorts. You cannot move it from wherever this 'box' it - it's essentially a forcefield of sorts that prevents that. Odd. Did this place have a 'stealing chairs' problem? On one side of the room is a huge monitor. It seems to be made by a company called 'Takimura Technologies', and allows the user, when it's on (most of the time, it's off unless one of the hosts is in the room), to simply point to screen, and it'll visualize whatever they have in their heads. Neat, huh? The walls and the ceilings themselves are mostly just plain, boring metal, but one of the walls seems to be a mini-aquarium of sorts. There's a glass wall, and behind it seems to be a display of many sorts of sea creatures, though you question how a whale could ever fit in that thing. Of course, there's a door leading out this place, too, but does that really need to be said? (edited)

Masami Okumura BOT 06-Nov-21 03:57 PM
Masami looks around to see that... oh. She glares at Rui. She's still clinging onto that grudge for dear life. On one hand... she can search for paths with them, but on the other-- it's Rui. Annoying, superiority complex, unhelpful, unwanted, inconsiderate and selfish. And yet... smart. Masami inhales, refusing to let the benefits overpower her pride and hurt. It's irrational... it's extremely irrational for Masami to team up with Rui. But... she made a promise, too. She wants to go home, sick and tired of this cage. She inhales, her chest feels painful as she pushes over the limits for a bit before exhaling audibly. Her glare disappears with her head turning to face the now dead Chichi. Oh how much she loathes what she's going to say at the moment.
"...Seems like you and I are the only ones who're planning to... get Chunyu that book he wanted from the library so badly."
She hopes Rui picks up on what she's trying to say. (edited)
